//! gnosis-antiqueue: AMQP-shaped broker on top of the FOIL Stoplight
//! scheduler. The defining move is that there is *no in-memory queue*.
//! Producers are rate-gated by the corridor's published green-window
//! calendar (per `Gnosis.Civil.QuasicrystalStoplightTiming`). Consumers
//! declare a Stoplight, the broker hands each `basic.publish` an
//! earliest-green start tick, and the message is dispatched to the
//! handler on that tick. Bounded depth by construction.
//!
//! ## Why "antiqueue"
//!
//! A queue is entropic accumulation: tasks pile up under load and the
//! resource drains FIFO. The depth is a *symptom* of poor scheduling.
//! The FOIL Stoplight inverts the regime: the resource publishes a
//! calendar of green windows and producers tile into it deterministically.
//! There is no waiting line; there is a schedule. The measured 5.07×
//! p99 win at the TS reference (`foil-runtime/bench.ts`) is the receipt
//! that the regime change actually took.
//!
//! ## AMQP mapping
//!
//! | AMQP operation       | gnosis-antiqueue          | Mechanism |
//! | -------------------- | ------------------------- | --------- |
//! | `exchange.publish`   | `Producer::publish`       | gated by `corridor_all_green` |
//! | `exchange.publish` (cost-aware) | `Producer::publish_certified` | value-door crossover: cheap=inline (RED), heavy=stagger (GREEN) |
//! | `queue.declare`      | `Broker::declare_consumer`| no buffer; handler tied to a Stoplight |
//! | `basic.qos prefetch` | `Stoplight::green` width  | wider green = wider prefetch |
//! | `basic.qos prefetch_size` | `QosSpec::handler_cost_ns` | value-door cost cert read by the cost-aware publish |
//! | `basic.ack`          | auto-ack at handler return| no explicit ack frame |
//! | `basic.nack`         | `phase_feedback`          | widens upstream offset |
//! | `exchange` types     | `Direct`/`Topic`/`Headers`/`Fanout` | corridor topology |
//! | DLX                  | `vent` combiner           | mock; tie to Task #8 vent |
//!
//! ## Cross-references
//!
//! - `Gnosis.Civil.QuasicrystalStoplightTiming` — corridor algebra (`Stoplight`,
//!   `seesGreen`, `corridorAllGreen`, `phaseCompensatingOffset`).
//! - `Gnosis.WankelEngineTheorem.FiveForceLifecycleStage` — chamber assignment
//!   (intake / compression / ignition / exhaust / interference) consumed by
//!   the `Channel` to label per-corridor flow stages.
//! - `gnosis-frf` (Task #11) — underlying lock-free dispatch and Stoplight
//!   scheduler. This crate is a downstream consumer; we do *not* duplicate
//!   the algebra here, we re-export it.

